external_knowledge:
High-income customers refer to those in the "High Income" segment; High-income is typically considered as an annual income of $100,000 or more; 
Accepted campaign 5 refers to customers who indicated acceptance of the promotional campaign 5; 
The average monthly spending amounts are calculated based on the total amount spent in purchases.

- 'High-value customers' refers to customers who belong to the 'High Value Customers' segment;
- 'Found at least one golden ticket' refers to customers who have accepted at least one campaign (i.e., accepted_cmp1, accepted_cmp2, accepted_cmp3, accepted_cmp4, or accepted_cmp5 is 1);
- 'Set sail with our crew' refers to customers who have made purchases (i.e., are present in the purchases table);
- 'Treasure unearthed' refers to the total amount spent by customers.

sql:
SELECT SUM(num_web_visits_month) AS total_web_visits
FROM web_activity
WHERE activity_date LIKE '2023-10-%';

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM customer_segments
WHERE segment_name = 'High Income';
